(42, 4, 43, 23, 42, 1, 4, 'preach the kingdom of God', 'Connection of Mission and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the mission of bringing forth judgment, with Luke highlighting the preaching of the kingdom of God and Isaiah describing the servant who will bring forth judgment to the Gentiles. This connection highlights the continuity of God''s purpose through Jesus as the fulfillment of the prophetic servant.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 43, 23, 61, 1, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Preaching and Anointing', 'This connection highlights the theme of preaching as both Jesus in Luke and the speaker in Isaiah emphasize the mission to bring good news and comfort to the oppressed. Both passages reflect a divine commissioning to proclaim hope and healing.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 44, 40, 4, 23, 23, 'in the synagogues of Galilee', 'Jesus'' Ministry in Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' active ministry in Galilee, highlighting his teaching and preaching in synagogues. The connection illustrates the continuity of his mission and the focus on the region.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 44, 41, 1, 39, 39, 'preached in the synagogues of Galilee', 'Preaching in Galilee Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' preaching in synagogues throughout Galilee. This connection highlights the continuity of His ministry focus in the region.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 44, 42, 4, 15, 15, NULL, 'Teaching in Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' teaching in synagogues, highlighting his active ministry in Galilee. The mention of being ''glorified of all'' in the second passage suggests a positive reception of his teachings.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 1, 41, 1, 16, 20, 'the lake of Gennesaret', 'Calling of the Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ministry by the water, where he engages with fishermen. The act of calling Simon, Andrew, James, and John to follow him connects their profession as fishers to their new role as ''fishers of men.''', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 1, 40, 4, 18, 22, 'the lake of Gennesaret', 'Calling of the Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ministry by the sea, where he calls his first disciples. The setting by the lake of Gennesaret in Luke parallels the sea of Galilee in Matthew, highlighting the significance of this location in Jesus'' early ministry.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 1, 41, 3, 9, 9, 'the people pressed upon him', 'Crowds and Jesus'' Response', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of a multitude pressing upon Jesus. In Luke, the people press to hear him, while in Mark, he instructs his disciples to prepare a small ship to avoid being thronged.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 1, 40, 14, 34, 34, 'lake of Gennesaret', 'Connection through Gennesaret', 'Both passages emphasize the location of Gennesaret, linking the ministry of Jesus in Luke with his arrival in Matthew. This connection highlights the significance of the lake as a setting for Jesus'' interactions with the people.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 1, 5, 3, 17, 17, 'lake of Gennesaret', 'Geographical Significance of Gennesaret', 'Both passages emphasize geographical locations significant to the narrative. The lake of Gennesaret in Luke is linked to the region mentioned in Deuteronomy, highlighting the importance of these areas in biblical events.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 1, 6, 12, 3, 3, 'lake of Gennesaret', 'Geographical Significance of Water Bodies', 'Both passages emphasize bodies of water, with Luke mentioning the lake of Gennesaret and Joshua referencing the sea of Chinneroth. This connection highlights the importance of these locations in biblical narratives.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 1, 4, 34, 11, 11, 'lake of Gennesaret', 'Geographical Significance of Borders', 'This connection highlights the geographical importance of bodies of water in both passages. The ''lake of Gennesaret'' in Luke and the ''sea of Chinnereth'' in Numbers both refer to significant bodies of water in the region, emphasizing their role in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 2, 41, 1, 19, 19, 'washing their nets', 'Connection of Fishing Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the activity of fishermen with their nets. In Luke, the fishermen are washing their nets, while in Mark, they are mending their nets, highlighting their ongoing work in fishing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 2, 40, 4, 21, 21, 'washing their nets', 'Fishermen and Net Work', 'Both passages emphasize fishermen engaged in net work. Luke mentions fishermen washing their nets, while Matthew describes them mending their nets, highlighting their occupation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 3, 40, 4, 18, 18, 'Simon’s', 'Connection of Simon Peter''s Calling', 'Both passages emphasize Simon''s role as a fisherman. In Luke, Jesus uses Simon''s ship to teach, while in Matthew, Simon is introduced as a fisherman. This connection highlights the significance of Simon''s profession in the context of his calling.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 3, 40, 13, 1, 2, 'sat down, and taught the people', 'Teaching from a Ship', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus teaching from a ship, highlighting his use of the water as a platform to address large crowds. This connection illustrates a common method of Jesus'' ministry, where he utilizes the environment to engage with the people.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 3, 41, 4, 1, 2, NULL, 'Teaching from a Ship', 'This connection highlights the act of teaching from a ship in both passages. Both Jesus enters a ship to address the crowd gathered by the sea, emphasizing his method of teaching in a maritime setting.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 3, 43, 1, 41, 42, 'Simon’s', 'Call of Simon Peter', 'This connection highlights the significance of Simon''s role in both passages. In Luke, Simon is introduced as a fisherman who becomes a disciple, while in John, he is identified as Simon, the brother of Andrew, who is called to follow Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 3, 43, 8, 2, 2, 'he sat down, and taught', 'Teaching from a Position of Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus teaching the people while seated, indicating a position of authority. In Luke, he teaches from a ship, while in John, he teaches in the temple.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 4, 43, 21, 6, 6, 'let down your nets for a draught', 'Miraculous Catch of Fish', 'Both passages emphasize the act of casting nets and the resulting abundance of fish. This connection highlights the miraculous nature of Jesus'' guidance in fishing, showcasing His authority and power.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 4, 40, 17, 27, 27, 'let down your nets for a draught', 'Connection of Fishing and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the act of fishing as a means of provision. In Luke, Simon is instructed to let down his nets, while in Matthew, a fish is used to provide money. This connection highlights the theme of divine provision through fishing.', 'theme', 0.363, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 5, 43, 2, 5, 5, 'at thy word I will let down the net', 'Obedience to Divine Instruction', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to divine instruction. Both passages emphasize the importance of acting on the word of authority, whether it be Jesus or His mother.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 5, 43, 15, 14, 14, 'at thy word I will let down the net', 'Obedience to Command', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to authority. In Luke, Simon obeys Jesus'' command despite previous failure, while in John, obedience to Jesus'' commands is a condition for friendship.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 5, 42, 6, 46, 48, 'at thy word I will let down the net', 'Obedience to God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to God''s commands. In Luke 5:5, Simon obeys Jesus'' instruction despite prior failure, while Luke 6:46-48 emphasizes the importance of doing what Jesus says as a foundation for stability.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 5, 12, 5, 10, 14, 'at thy word I will let down the net', 'Obedience to Divine Instruction', 'Both passages emphasize obedience to God''s word despite initial doubt. Simon Peter''s willingness to let down the net and Naaman''s eventual compliance to wash in the Jordan illustrate a theme of faith in following divine commands.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 5, 26, 37, 4, 7, 'at thy word I will let down the net', 'Obedience to God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of responding to God''s command. In both passages, the characters act upon the word of the Lord, leading to miraculous outcomes.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 5, 19, 127, 1, 2, 'toiled all the night', 'Labor and Divine Assistance', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of labor without divine support. Simon''s acknowledgment of toil in Luke reflects the sentiment in Psalms that labor is in vain unless the Lord is involved.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 5, 26, 37, 11, 12, 'nevertheless at thy word', 'Hope and Renewal', 'This connection highlights the theme of hope in both passages. In Luke, Simon expresses faith despite failure, while Ezekiel conveys God''s promise of restoration to Israel, emphasizing renewal and revival.', 'theme', 0.391, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 6, 43, 21, 6, 11, 'great multitude of fishes', 'Miraculous Catch of Fish', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous catch of fish, showcasing the power of Jesus in guiding the disciples to a bountiful harvest. In both instances, the nets are filled to the point of breaking, highlighting the abundance provided by Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 6, 46, 15, 58, 58, NULL, 'Abundance in Labor for the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of fruitful labor. In Luke, the disciples'' efforts result in a great multitude, while in Corinthians, believers are encouraged to abound in their work, knowing it is not in vain.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
